A judge may, by order, designate a magistrate to conduct hearings, including evidentiary hearings, and to submit to the judge proposed findings of fact and recommendations for the disposition of any matter excepted under this section.

Toby 2025-01-23 09:01 a.m.
Ok hi guys. I do apologise for the delay in ruling on the MTD. I don't have the time to write out a full detailed ruling so I'll do it in a discord message.

I'm denying the motion to dismiss on the following grounds:

I find that the charge of voluntary manslaughter is sufficient in it's language and satisfies the core element of the offence of voluntary manslaughter, also the reference to 'sudden quarrel' does adequately negate malice aforethought. I also find that establishing the defendants intent in regards to who they may or may not have intended to hit is a matter for trial.

Accordingly the motion to dismiss is denied.

I will also stipulate that this ruling has the approval of the residing district judge @krabz.
